le\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527234\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 26, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104eod1665702920617.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eod1665702920617.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eod1665702920617.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"eod1665702920617\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Field-Level Validation\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"eod1665702920617__field_level_validation_139514\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Validation of a field can be initiated the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">validatefield</span> ProcScript statement, by an event that changes focus, or by cascading validation from a higher level of the component or application.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eod1665702920617__p_d45227e1_d45228e1_d45229e1\">The conditions for field validation are either:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eod1665702920617__li_d22478e1_d22479e1_d22480e1\">Field data has been modified, and the field has not yet been validated successfully, or\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eod1665702920617__li_d22481e1_d22482e1_d22483e1\">Validation is demanded for the field by setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$fieldcheck</span>.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eod1665702920617__topic_d29337e1_d29338e1_d29339e1_d29340e1_d29341e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1043492e71\">\n                       \n Validation Process\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eod1665702920617__p_d45233e1_d45234e1_d45235e1\">The process for validating a field is as follows:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eod1665702920617__li_d22484e1_d22485e1_d22486e1\">Uniface carries out declarative checks for the field, based on the field syntax, data type, and ValRep lists.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eod1665702920617__li_d22487e1_d22488e1_d22489e1\">Uniface activates the validate trigger for the field, and executes procedural validation ProcScript written in the trigger.\n </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jwi1665702576586.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>validatefield</a><p>Validate a field of the current occurrence.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/swr1665702599962.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$fieldcheck</a><p>Return or set the requirement for field validation.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tcu1665702530867.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Data Types</a><p>Data types are classifications for data containers, such as fields, variables, parameters, and return values. They define the characteristics of the data and determine how the data is handled during processing and storage.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527234\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527234\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Field-Level Validation Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 26, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Field-Level Validation Validation of a field can be initiated the validatefield ProcScript statement, by an event that changes focus, or by cascading validation from a higher level of the component or application. The conditions for field validation are either: Field data has been modified, and the field has not yet been validated successfully, or Validation is demanded for the field by setting $fieldcheck . Validation Process The process for validating a field is as follows: Uniface carries out declarative checks for the field, based on the field syntax, data type, and ValRep lists. Uniface activates the validate trigger for the field, and executes procedural validation ProcScript written in the trigger. Related Links validatefield Validate a field of the current occurrence. $fieldcheck Return or set the requirement for field validation. Data Types Data types are classifications for data containers, such as fields, variables, parameters, and return values. They define the characteristics of the data and determine how the data is handled during processing and storage. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}